<pdd-reason>Defines the `pdd contracts check` CLI group for deterministic contract checks.</pdd-reason>

<pdd-dependency>contract_check_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_apply_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

% Write `pdd/commands/contracts.py`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Requirements
- Implement `@click.group(name="contracts")` with a `check` subcommand.
- `contracts check TARGET` accepts file or directory, plus optional `--stories` directory.
- Support `--json` output and `--strict` warning escalation.
- Exit codes: 0 clean, 1 warnings, 2 errors or strict warnings.
- Use `pdd.contract_check` public API for evaluation (no LLM calls).
- Add apply flags to `contracts check`:
  - `--interactive` flag (required with `--apply`)
  - `--apply` flag (required with `--interactive`; delegates to `run_checkup_apply` with patches from contract check findings — missing vocabulary or coverage entries)
  - `--dry-run` flag (diff preview only; no file writes)
  - `--force-apply` flag (apply even when deterministic errors exist)
  - `--verify-strict` flag (re-run `contract check --strict` on touched prompts post-apply; propagate exit code)
  - When `--apply` is present without `--interactive`, MUST raise `click.UsageError` ("--apply requires --interactive") before evaluating any contract checks.
  - When `--apply` and `--interactive` are both set, pass contract-check findings as `ApplyPatch` objects to `run_checkup_apply`.

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/commands/contracts.py`
